        section#descricao.mt-5
            .container
                .decptext.text-center
                    h1 Administration & Business

                .decptext.text-start        
                    p.lead.fw-bold The diploma of higher professional technician in Administration and Business is conferred to students who demonstrate, in this area:
                    p.lead a) possess knowledge and comprehension skills; 
                    p.lead b) know how to apply, in professional contexts, the knowledge and comprehension skills acquired;
                    p.lead c) have the ability to identify and use information to respond to well-defined concrete and abstract problems;
                    p.lead d) possess skills that enable them to communicate about their understanding of issues, skills and activities with their peers, supervisors and clients;
                    p.lead e) Possess learning skills that allow them to pursue studies with some autonomy.

        section#perfil.mt-5
            .container
                .decptext.text-center 
                    h2 Profile of the study program

                .decptext.text-start
                    p.lead Plan, coordinate and execute the operations associated with the various functional areas of public and private organizations, contributing to the administrative management of these entities and to the development of the businesses that sustain them.


        section#diplomados.mt-5
        .container
            .decptext.text-center 
                h2 Occupational profile of graduates

            .decptext.text-start
                p.lead.fw-bold The Higher Technical Professional Course in Administration and Business is part of the training area of Business Sciences and Law, and its graduates are prepared to perform technical functions, within the scope of the study program profile:
                p.lead - Plan, organize, execute and control the administrative activities inherent to the different functional areas of the public and private organizations in which it provides services.
                p.lead - Design, develop and monitor the implementation of businesses that support the strategies defined for organizations.
                p.lead - Manage, autonomously, the workflow inherent to the operation of the administrative and secretarial services.
                p.lead - Coordinate the financial and strategic management of the negotiation area of the organizations.
                p.lead - Coordinate the administrative management of human resources.
                p.lead - Manage the information received and produced, applying the appropriate computer applications to administrative management.
                p.lead - Manage and promote commercial management and negotiation techniques.
                p.lead - Promote and manage innovation and entrepreneurship in organizations.
                p.lead - Plan and analyze the financial activity of the organization.
                p.lead - Coordinate business-related tasks of and with public organizations.



